## [13] "HAR1"     "HAR3"     "SMOKE"    "TCP"      "HBP"

The National Health and Nutrition Survey (NHANES3.DAT) contains 17030 observations and 16 variables. (delete)SDPPSU6: Pseudo-PSU: 1, 2. (delete)SDPSTRA6: Pseudo-stratum: 01-49 (delete)WTPFHX6: Statistical weight: 225.93-139744.9 HSAGEIR: Age: years HSSEX: Sex: 0=Female, 1=Male DMARACER: Race: 1=White, 2=Black, 3=Other. BMPWTLBS: Body Weight: pounds BMPHTIN: Standing Height: inches (delete)PEPMNK1R: Average Systolic BP: mm Hg PEPMNK5R: Average Diastolic BP: mm Hg (delete)HAR1: Has repondent smoked > 100 cigarettes in life: 1=Yes, 2=No (delete)HAR3: Does respondent smoke cigarettes now: 1=Yes, 2=No SMOKE: Smoking: 1=if HAR1=2, 2=if HAR1=1&HAR3=2, 3=if HAR1=1&HAR3=1 TCP: Serum Cholesterol: mg/100 ml HBP: High Blood Pressure: 0 if PEPMNK1R <=140, 1 if PEPMNK1R > 140

data<-data[-dim(data)[1],]
data<-data[,-c(1,2,3,4,13,14)]
data<-na.omit(data)
#View(data)
#png("fig/SBP-DBP.png",width = 480, height = 400, units = "px")
plot(data[data$HBP==0,]$PEPMNK1R, data[data$HBP==0,]$PEPMNK5R,col = "#92C5DE" ,xlim=c(60,250), ylim=c(10,150),xlab='Average Systolic BP (mm Hg)', ylab='Average Diastolic BP (mm Hg)', main='Diastolic BP vs. Systolic BP')
points(data[data$HBP==1,]$PEPMNK1R, data[data$HBP==1,]$PEPMNK5R,col = "#FF9999")
abline(v=140, lwd=3, lty=2)
legend(60,150,legend=c("HBP","No HBP"), col=c("#FF9999","#92C5DE"), pch=c("o","o"), ncol=1)

HBP<-data$HBP
age<-data$HSAGEIR
sex<-as.factor(data$HSSEX)
race<-as.factor(data$DMARACER)
smoke<-as.factor(data$SMOKE)
weight<-data$BMPWTLBS
height<-data$BMPHTIN
chole<-data$TCP
